{
  "stem": "20711.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It's between the house and backyard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It's a big, arched [? wave. ?] And she disappeared in one of them so I couldn't talk to her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But I was ready to declare my friendship after that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But anyway, it was fun time, too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We were very concerned of what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But thanks to one of the policeman who was also sympathetic and asked us why we are here, and my mom asked her-- asked him to take a message to my uncle.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And once my uncle find out we are in this prison, he started to move mountains to get us out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And he happened to be in a friendly term with the governor of the county.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And he approached the governor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And it just happened to have a loophole in the Jewish laws during that period, which may not last, then, very long, but that was a loophole, a kind of easement, for half-breeds, like I was considered to.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And he gave a paper to my uncle, which allowed my uncle to pick us up and take us out of the prison.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "So he came, and he rescued us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And we didn't have to report anyplace.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "He wanted us immediately to go to his house, but it wouldn't be safe any place on a long run.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mom decided as long as we have this paper which allow us to be free, she would prefer to go home and look around the house and change clothes, pick up fresh things, and get prepared for the next steps and see Grandmother and the aunts and everybody.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that's what we did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went back home, but we kept a very low profile.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The house was constantly supervised by my family, my Catholic family.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
